“However, in the event that the coach had braked suddenly, the laws of physics would obviously apply.
In the same way as in an urban bus or in a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of the stewards by internal prescriptions,” he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not settled.
Jančura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only coach carrier to offer steward services.
He hires two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their job as a risky job.
“Nevertheless, as soon as I feel it is a risky job, I will delete it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper upon boarding.
It would also lower costs,&quot; he said.
The concern for security is the reason given by the director of the Asiana Alexeï Litvine for the absence of stewards in his vehicles, which provides, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
&quot;We don&#39;t have hostesses. We&#39;ve been against it from the start.
Sooner or later it will end in a fatal accident,&quot; he told Týden.cz a year ago.
A huge tragedy has happened
A young stewardess from the Pilsen region, who had worked for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the hard shoulder without using a turn signal and blocked the way to the coach.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he grazed him on his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards have been sold.
&quot;In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked.&quot;
The company intends to file a complaint against the driver of the truck.
For the compensation of the family of the young girl, the agency will not wait for the judgment of the court, but with regard to the financial compensation, it also counts on the culprit.
A change in the law?
Not in sight
A modification of the law, which has been in the process of being drawn up for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide clarification as to the movements of the stewards on board the coach.
“However, it did not come to any conclusion on this point.
To tell the truth, she is not so interested in buses, but rather in the points system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of mobile phones while driving,&quot; says expert Hořín.
&quot;The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of stewards as something that would fundamentally jeopardize the safety of passengers,&quot; concludes spokesman Hanzelka, specifying that the control of coach safety is under the power of the police and the office for occupational safety.
