The &#39;bee car&#39; that avoids collisions
To advance the development of technologies for the prevention of accidents, Nissan was inspired, this time, by nature, in particular bees.
The Japanese company has created a robot which, by imitating the flight of bees, avoids accidents.
It&#39;s called Bio-Mimetic Car Robot Drive, or BR23C, and represents the first steps in collision avoidance technologies.
Engineers from the Advanced Technical Center of Nissan Motor Co. made this little robot in collaboration with the Center for Advanced Science and Technology Research at the prestigious University of Tokyo, Japan.
According to Kazuhiro Doi, general manager of PR for Technology and Brand Management Research and Development, the BR23C represents the rise of the Nissan Safety Shield.
This robot will enable the brand&#39;s vehicles to prevent collisions.
During its flight, each bee creates its own personal space in an oval shape that closely resembles the Nissan security shield.
But most important are the bee&#39;s compound eyes, which can see over 300 degrees and in all directions, allowing it to fly uninterrupted within its own personal space.
To recreate this visual function, engineers developed something called a Laser Range Finder.
This detects obstacles within a distance of two meters and within a radius of 180 degrees, calculates the distance to this object and sends a signal to the microprocessor, immediately, to avoid the obstacle.
&quot;The moment it detects an obstacle, the little robot will imitate the movements of a bee and immediately change direction by turning its wheels 90 degrees or more to avoid collision.
The biggest difference from any other existing system is that the evasive maneuver is totally instinctive.
If this were the case, the robot would not be able to react quickly enough to avoid obstacles,” explains Toshiyuki Andoh, director of the Movement Laboratory and main engineer of this project.
Unlike a bee, the robot cannot be hijacked up or down, or diagonally; he can only move in two dimensions and according to what his wheels allow him and not in infinite directions like the bees.
For this reason, Nissan has used a function of rotation, but also of acceleration and deceleration, so that the small robot can avoid obstacles.
“Every second this device only needs to process information and act on that data.
It does not need to store information or intuitive logics of previous operations, which is why it can work continuously with only a few dozen KB of memory.
It may come as a surprise, but we&#39;re not talking about gigabytes of memory, or even megabytes.&quot;
This represents the first development of new instant collision avoidance technologies, a technology that will be introduced in production cars in about ten years according to Nissan.
The robot works with lithium-polymer batteries, which are lighter and last longer than lithium-ion batteries.
The other possible application of this technology in the future could be the adaptation of this device on a GPS satellite navigation system to guide the driver to his destination avoiding obstacles on the road.
Repeat drink-driving offenders will have to install the &#39;alcolock&#39; system
The Minister of the Interior wants the driver who has had more than three administrative sanctions for alcohol, to have to install in his vehicle a system which prevents starting the vehicle in a state of intoxication, or if he is not breathing.
The initiative was already announced last June and it now appears in the report of the Minister of State in which this initiative is considered as a pilot project which will last one year.
Its aim is the reintegration of the driver by offering him road rehabilitation courses.
The Minister of State in charge of road safety but also the General Directorate of Road Safety and the Technological Institute Foundation for Automobile Safety will participate in this initiative.
According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of motorists arrested for having driven more than once in a state of intoxication, take the car back.
The alcolock would avoid this since it is a system connected to the vehicle which measures the alcohol level in the breath and prevents the vehicle from being started if the driver does not breathe before; or when the driver&#39;s alcohol level is higher than permitted.
