talking while sleeping
A few children talk during the night.
I am not referring to those who wake up wide awake telling us about something that happened the day before, but to children who talk in their sleep.
The first time it happens it may surprise you, but in reality it doesn&#39;t matter.
It is a benign alteration of sleep which is called somniloquy.
It is quite common, especially in children and adolescents.
It is sure that there is more than one who speaks during the night.
This phenomenon can appear very sporadically (once in a lifetime, for example, associated with an episode of high fever), or more periodically (every day, once a week, once a month, etc.), the day after the child does not remember anything.
There is no single cause that determines its occurrence
They are often linked to other sleep disturbances such as nightmares, night terrors, nocturnal enuresis (wetting the bed) or sleepwalking, but this is not always the case.
As we have already said before, they can also be associated with very high fevers, situations of stress or over-excitement.
Either way, it&#39;s a little-studied phenomenon.
The intensity with which it occurs is also highly variable.
He may speak with a quiet little voice, with isolated words, whispers or on the contrary with cries, tears, long speeches...
In case the sleep talking becomes very frequent, it would be wise to observe the child and consult a specialist, to check if there is a problem that causes a lot of anxiety and in order to obtain an explanation for this problem. .
We said it&#39;s a mild impairment, so there&#39;s no treatment unless it&#39;s related to another sleep impairment that can be cured (for example, if it&#39;s related to sleep apnea or stress).
What can be done is to take into account a number of very simple preventive measures such as:
Try not to excite the child before going to sleep.
Therefore look for quiet games and avoid programs or television series that are more or less violent.
With children who are very nervous and find it difficult to relax, relaxation techniques can be used to help them calm down internally.
This will allow the child to have a more peaceful sleep.
As soon as sleep talking appears try to remain calm.
Remember that they are harmless for the child and that the next day he will not remember what happened.
Useful tips
Don&#39;t wake him up.
It&#39;s useless since he&#39;s unconscious and you would wake him up.
Even if he talks, he sleeps and therefore rests.
Remember that if he shows himself very anxious several times, it is advisable to consult a doctor or to check what causes so much anxiety in the child.
If you understand what he is saying (which is unusual), don&#39;t be tempted to question him for information.
You won&#39;t get anything, because while sleeping, he is not conscious to be able to organize his thoughts.
Also, you&#39;ll hear what he&#39;s saying, but you won&#39;t know what he&#39;s dreaming about, so be careful how you interpret the information and what conclusions you draw from it.
Never tell the child that you can interrogate him at night to find out his secrets.
Not even joking.
This causes a lot of anxiety.
In conclusion, don&#39;t worry, it&#39;s nothing too bad, it&#39;s an episode that only lasts a few minutes.
