Anyone who wants to hide something, or at least wants to try to circumvent Google&#39;s monopoly, can do so (starting, for example, with Scroogle, using the Google search system, but, at the same time, intentionally leaving no trace ).
The number of people who deliberately do not register on public pages so that it is not possible to find them is not the least. Google online services, from word processing to image processing, to reading information can be replaced by alternative versions, which are not attached to huge server farms and which do not assemble not our best profile, having existed until this day.
