The first of these phenomena is the re-actualization, the extraordinary revival, of the double category State-sovereign, in relation to a sort of renationalisation of the economy.
The crisis, in fact, is a crisis of banking and financial institutions which obviously have close relations with foreign countries, but which, above all, are involved on a large scale, the balance sheets of the people and families who live in one country, in one state.
