. Paradoxically, in fact, while we were convinced that we had now entered the realm of the network, of ever more sophisticated technology, of the non-material, convinced that globalized finance was now destined to dominate the world, we realized all of a sudden, that our future will on the contrary have to settle its accounts ever more often with relatively unmaterial things like water, crops, oil.
