Open Office, here is the third edition of the &quot;anti-Microsoft&quot; package
It&#39;s the day of the release of OpenOffice.org.3.0, the open source personal productivity suite that aims to reach ever and even more users, from home to office, from professionals to public administration, offering a free alternative to the most famous Microsoft Office.
Following almost a year of work, carried out by volunteer developers, supervised by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office package is being shown to the general public with various new features: from the welcome screen, and the revised interface that has become less austere, to other more important ones, such as the compatibility born for the operating system Apple Mac OS X, and the support for the new format ODF (Open Document Format) 1.2, the latest ISO standard version.
Open Office has paid particular attention to the interaction with the Office 2007 suite, and it is indeed possible to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx.)
Also interesting are some functions specific to certain modules, such as the one that allows to reduce the dimensions of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example, to send them by e-mail, or to import PDF files into the graphic elaboration module, preserving the original appearance of the page.
Also on this front, it is possible to create &quot;hybrid PDF&quot; documents that unite the typical graphic of the Adobe format with the elements of a spreadsheet or a text editor.
The collaboration between several people is an element that has had various improvements inside the applications: in the spreadsheet, various users can intervene, avoiding conflicts on the modifications, in the elaboration of texts, because to each collaborator is assigned a comment color for better recognition during the revision phase.
Some companies are even working to bring certain features of OpenOffice to the web (on the cloud), and in the next few weeks they should release the final result.
The Italian version can be downloaded at the address http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html and is added to the English version which was on the mirror since Friday.
Besides Windows and Mac OS, the suite is also available as usual for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation CD can be shipped to your home or workplace.
And if the theme of free can be a way to spread it in homes, it is precisely in business, that Open Office the suite tries the big challenge, being able to already count on various projects carried out in the public administration and the schools.
Not to mention the realities that offer a training, consultation and assistance service, ideal for small and medium-sized businesses, which could also open up to business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for Word&#39;s video writing equivalent; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for PowerPoint rival presentations; Dbase, such as the famous Access, is the program that allows you to work on databases; finally Drwa is the graphics module.
Objective for 2008, to arrive at 5 million downloads, and considering that today there are almost 3 million and 600 miles, it is probable that with the release of the new version, we can even exceed the expected figure
