Found the plane of Steve Fossett, the billionaire who disappeared a year ago.
The wreckage of Steve Fosset&#39;s plane, the billionaire who disappeared on September 3, 2007 while flying over the Nevada desert, has been found.
The debris was found on a plateau 3,000 meters above sea level in the Sierra Nevada area of Mammonth Lakes, on the California-Nevada border.
Inside the plane, however, no human remains.
Madera County Sheriff John Anderson dismissed any lingering doubts: &quot;The plane was located, we dispatched a team, and now we have confirmation that it is indeed the one Steve Fosset was on. was traveling the day he disappeared,&quot; he told a news conference.
The sheriff therefore specified that no human remains were found either on the plane or in the surroundings.
In February, the 63-year-old billionaire was considered deceased.
The US Transportation Safety Board (Ntsb) reported that a few hours after the wreckage was spotted, a team of investigators sent to the scene identified the aircraft: it is indeed the Bellanca 8kcab, disappeared on September 3, 2007, when Fosset took off from Yerington, Nevada for a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, still in California, not far from the Nevada border, some of Fosset&#39;s personal effects were found by a couple near their home in Mammoth Lakes.
They are two documents bearing Fosset&#39;s name, both issued by the Federal Aviation Administration of Illinois, cash and a sweater.
Fossett&#39;s research was halted a month after his disappearance.
The billionaire had earned a place in history thanks to a long series of records.
At the sixth attempt, he became in 2002, the first man to complete the world tour on an aerostatic balloon: two weeks of solo flight.
Three years later, he had traveled around the world by plane and nonstop.
Among all these records, also that of having flown at a height of 15,445 meters, over the Andes, but with a co-pilot.
